Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 - 12/2018]
Title: EXTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: FRONT BUMPER: REASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2018 MY Prius [11/2015 - 12/2018]

REASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT LH

(a) Engage the claw as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Engage the clip as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(c) Install the front bumper side support LH with the bolt.

Torque:

5.4 Nm {55 kgfcm, 48 inlbf}

2. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

3. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION LH

(a) Install the front bumper extension LH with the 4 bolts.

Torque:

12 Nm {122 kgfcm, 9 ftlbf}

4. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

5. INSTALL NO. 2 FRONT BUMPER REINFORCEMENT

(a) Install the No. 2 front bumper reinforcement with the 4 nuts.

Torque:

30 Nm {306 kgfcm, 22 ftlbf}

6. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER REINFORCEMENT SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the 2 guides.

(b) Install the front bumper reinforcement sub-assembly with the 8 bolts.

Torque:

50 Nm {510 kgfcm, 37 ftlbf}

(c) Engage the 11 clamps.

7. INSTALL RADIATOR SHUTTER SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

8. INSTALL LOWER FRONT BUMPER ABSORBER

(a) Install the lower front bumper absorber with the 3 clips.

9. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER ENERGY ABSORBER

(a) Install the front bumper energy absorber as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

10. INSTALL FRONT ENERGY ABSORBER MOUNTING REINFORCEMENT LH

(a) Install the front energy absorber mounting reinforcement LH as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

11. INSTALL FRONT ENERGY ABSORBER MOUNTING REINFORCEMENT RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

12. INSTALL RADIATOR GRILLE EMBLEM ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the 2 guides and 2 claws as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Install the radiator grille emblem assembly with 2 new spring nuts.

13. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER HOLE COVER LH

(a) Engage the hook.

*a

Hook

Install in this Direction

(b) Engage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration to install the front bumper hole cover LH.

14. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER HOLE COVER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

15. INSTALL LOWER NO. 1 RADIATOR GRILLE

(a) Engage the 18 claws as shown in the illustration to install the lower No. 1 radiator grille.

Install in this Direction

16. INSTALL NO. 3 AIR CLEANER INLET

(a) Engage the 3 claws.

(b) Install the No. 3 air cleaner inlet with the 2 screws.

17. INSTALL RADIATOR GRILLE SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Engage the 15 claws as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Install the radiator grille sub-assembly with the 2 screws and 4 clips.

18. INSTALL HOOD TO FRONT END PANEL SEAL

(a) Remove the release paper from a new hood to front end panel seal.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(b) Engage the 2 clips and attach the double-sided tape to install the hood to front end panel seal.

Double-sided Tape

-

-

19. INSTALL FRONT FENDER LINER RETAINER

(a) Engage the 2 claws to install the 2 front fender liner retainers.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

20. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION LH

(a) Engage the claw.

(b) Install the front bumper extension LH with the 2 screws.

21. INSTALL FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

23. INSTALL FOG LIGHT ASSEMBLY RH (w/ Fog Light)

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

25. INSTALL NO. 3 ENGINE ROOM WIRE (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

(a) w/o Fog Light:

(1) Engage the 10 clamps to install the No. 3 engine room wire.

(b) w/ Fog Light:

(1) Engage the 10 clamps to install the No. 3 engine room wire.
